WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.440
I'm Buddy.

00:02.440 --> 00:03.480
Kelly.

00:03.480 --> 00:04.880
Actress.

00:04.880 --> 00:06.920
DANI: It's looking good.
Who's it for?

00:06.920 --> 00:08.560
Special commission.

00:08.560 --> 00:11.080
I just had sex with my best friend.

00:11.080 --> 00:13.960
If this isn't what you want...
No, it's not that.

00:13.960 --> 00:18.960
There was more wrong with it
than just him being my best mate.

00:18.960 --> 00:20.400
What if I don't get off?

00:20.400 --> 00:23.480
Then you do the time
and you keep your head down.

00:23.480 --> 00:25.240
TROTTER:
Everyone thinks Snap's the good guy

00:25.240 --> 00:27.560
and I'm the scrounging dickhead
who can't pay his debt.

00:27.560 --> 00:30.200
Get us a bloody proper house
to live in, Trot!

00:30.200 --> 00:31.560
I wanna prove myself.

00:31.560 --> 00:34.160
You're 21.
Isn't it time to get serious?

00:34.160 --> 00:39.520
Buddy and I would like to buy the
licence to sell Lightwave in the US.

00:39.520 --> 00:41.560
Have you got the money for this,
Newport?

00:41.560 --> 00:44.080
I'm talking US Dollars, Trot.

00:48.480 --> 00:51.480
(WATER LAPS)

01:04.320 --> 01:06.320
(DOOR CLANKS SHUT)

01:07.960 --> 01:10.680
(EXHALES SOFTLY)

01:15.000 --> 01:16.520
Hey!

01:18.800 --> 01:20.560
(SNIFFLES)

01:21.560 --> 01:23.440
(CHUCKLES)

01:25.440 --> 01:28.280
Hey. I'll take this.

01:38.400 --> 01:42.040
(WAVES CRASH)

01:44.720 --> 01:46.680
Sorry, I know it's not like Auntie's.

01:46.680 --> 01:48.280
You can stay with us
as long as you want.

01:48.280 --> 01:49.520
Mm-hm.

01:49.520 --> 01:51.160
Or join her back in the city...

01:52.160 --> 01:53.680
Whatever you want, mate.

01:54.680 --> 01:56.200
I dunno.

01:57.200 --> 01:59.360
You don't have to make up your mind
just yet.

02:04.440 --> 02:07.080
The kids have been asking after you.

02:07.080 --> 02:09.080
And Choc.

02:12.160 --> 02:13.840
And...

02:13.840 --> 02:16.600
And Bear dropped that one by.

02:19.440 --> 02:23.120
Alrighty. Payday, people!

02:23.120 --> 02:25.080
Thanks for your work this week.

02:25.080 --> 02:27.280
Winkle, there you go.
Overtime's in there too, mate.

02:27.280 --> 02:28.320
Ah, finally!

02:28.320 --> 02:29.880
Easy.

02:29.880 --> 02:31.480
Let's all be a little grateful

02:31.480 --> 02:33.600
that that southerly's
been blowing this week, huh,

02:33.600 --> 02:36.960
so we could spend
a little bit more time indoors.

02:36.960 --> 02:38.480
Reggie.

02:38.480 --> 02:40.640
You're not Father fuckin' Christmas,
Snap.

02:40.640 --> 02:42.360
You're supposed to pay your staff
each week.

02:42.360 --> 02:46.240
(SEWING MACHINE WHIRRS)

02:47.240 --> 02:50.560
Hey! Here he is!

02:51.560 --> 02:53.560
Welcome home.

02:59.640 --> 03:01.440
Keep it.

03:24.040 --> 03:25.840
(WAVES CRASH)

03:28.320 --> 03:31.040
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

03:32.040 --> 03:33.840
(BIRDS SQUAWK)

03:36.600 --> 03:38.880
SONG: # In the middle of the summer

03:38.880 --> 03:42.360
# When the sun pours over
down in California

03:42.360 --> 03:46.120
# Gonna see
those friends of mine... #

03:46.120 --> 03:48.640
Hey-hey! Gina! My girl!

03:48.640 --> 03:49.800
Good to see you!

03:50.800 --> 03:52.440
Good to see YOU.

03:54.920 --> 03:57.360
Oh! Let me help you with that.

03:57.360 --> 04:00.440
OK, oh! I got it.

04:00.440 --> 04:02.480
Hey!
Alright.

04:04.280 --> 04:05.800
OK.

04:06.920 --> 04:09.160
You see? Good quality.

04:09.160 --> 04:10.880
(CHUCKLES)

04:15.280 --> 04:16.680
Wait.

04:18.200 --> 04:20.600
This isn't the right logo.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.160
Really?

04:22.160 --> 04:23.800
Look.

04:23.800 --> 04:27.600
It's... It's to the east,
not to the west, you see?

04:27.600 --> 04:33.320
OK, well, it's, uh...like a sunrise,
not a sunset. It's more positive.

04:33.320 --> 04:36.960
We finished your order, OK? If you
wanna change it, it'll cost you.

04:36.960 --> 04:40.520
You did all the shorts like this?
Of course.

04:40.520 --> 04:44.640
Hey, hey, if you boys don't have the
money, we'll just keep the shorts.

04:44.640 --> 04:45.640
Hunter?

04:46.760 --> 04:48.720
Hunter, dude...

04:48.720 --> 04:50.040
Gina!

05:05.160 --> 05:07.240
Those two are yours too.

05:07.240 --> 05:09.480
Thank you! Have a nice day!

05:09.480 --> 05:11.800
Yeah. Thanks, Gina.

05:12.840 --> 05:13.840
OK.

05:15.640 --> 05:18.640
OK...I really don't think
it matters.

05:18.640 --> 05:20.760
It's a breach of the licence, Buddy.

05:20.760 --> 05:23.480
Even if we wanted to change it,
we can't afford to.

05:23.480 --> 05:25.440
Plus...Trotter'll never know.

05:25.440 --> 05:28.360
You know, out of sight, out of mind.

05:31.120 --> 05:34.120
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

05:38.920 --> 05:41.920
(MUSIC, CHATTER)

05:46.400 --> 05:49.920
(MUSIC, CHATTER)

06:11.680 --> 06:13.760
Uh... Beer, please.

06:37.840 --> 06:39.720
You're new.

06:45.560 --> 06:46.920
I'm Tash.

06:48.400 --> 06:49.760
Dani.

06:56.520 --> 06:59.520
(WAVES LAP)

07:40.080 --> 07:41.520
You should do it.

07:41.520 --> 07:43.240
(GASPS) Margaux!
(CHUCKLES)

07:43.240 --> 07:45.000
Mwah! Mwah!

07:45.000 --> 07:46.240
Where's Sharpie?

07:46.240 --> 07:48.800
Ah! I left him
screening his film up north.

07:48.800 --> 07:51.360
You know, the art of conversation
and Queensland grommets

07:51.360 --> 07:53.760
is not a good fit.
(LAUGHS)

07:54.760 --> 07:56.680
You look nice.

07:58.520 --> 08:00.320
So?

08:00.320 --> 08:01.520
What'd I miss?

08:03.120 --> 08:05.040
What is it?

08:07.640 --> 08:08.640
OK.

08:08.640 --> 08:12.280
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)
TRACY: Bye, kids!

08:12.280 --> 08:14.560
Yeah, sorry.

08:23.120 --> 08:25.200
What have you done?

08:25.200 --> 08:27.080
(CHUCKLES)

08:27.080 --> 08:31.800
It was a love letter from a wealthy
merchant banker to his new bride.

08:31.800 --> 08:33.760
It was going to be
their coastal retreat,

08:33.760 --> 08:36.880
but, tragically,
unforeseen circumstances intervened.

08:36.880 --> 08:39.360
Mm.
Did someone die here?

08:39.360 --> 08:40.920
No, it was divorce.

08:40.920 --> 08:42.480
He slept with the sister.

08:42.480 --> 08:44.080
It was a messy business.

08:44.080 --> 08:47.280
Just needs a new lick of paint,
new tiles on the roof,

08:47.280 --> 08:49.440
kitchen appliances,
curtains, carpets.

08:49.440 --> 08:50.920
You can really make it your own.

08:50.920 --> 08:53.880
What do you think?
(LAUGHS)

08:53.880 --> 08:55.920
You can't be serious.

08:55.920 --> 08:57.640
We can't afford this.

08:57.640 --> 08:58.960
Tell her, Glen.

08:58.960 --> 09:00.840
Congratulations!

09:00.840 --> 09:03.000
(LAUGHS)
(LAUGHS)

09:03.000 --> 09:04.640
You bought Dumbo?

09:04.640 --> 09:07.280
Babe, I got it for a steal.

09:07.280 --> 09:10.080
A long settlement. Half the deposit.

09:10.080 --> 09:12.440
Glen even threw in
the outdoor furniture.

09:12.440 --> 09:14.920
You bought Dumbo.
Don't call it that, Trace.

09:14.920 --> 09:17.000
Everyone calls it that, Trot!

09:17.000 --> 09:19.400
It's a white elephant!
Dumbo was grey, actually.

09:19.400 --> 09:21.480
Shut up, Glen.
Give us a minute, eh?

09:22.600 --> 09:25.480
This is a very good deal. Trust me.

09:25.480 --> 09:29.560
We are talking
EXTREMELY ugly divorce.

09:31.480 --> 09:33.880
Well, I thought you'd be happy.
No more living in the factory.

09:33.880 --> 09:36.480
How are we supposed to pay for this?
The US licence deal.

09:36.480 --> 09:39.720
You seriously think Buddy and Newbie
are gonna come up with 10 grand?

09:41.760 --> 09:43.120
They will.

09:47.720 --> 09:50.080
You seen that Sunny Steadman kid?

09:50.080 --> 09:53.240
I flowed him some Lightwaves, but we
should think about sponsoring him.

09:53.240 --> 09:56.080
Yeah, before or after
we pay Trotter's licence fee?

09:56.080 --> 09:58.280
Well, Sunny said he's headed
to Pipeline next week.

09:58.280 --> 09:59.960
That's a guaranteed front cover.

09:59.960 --> 10:02.640
A front cover is not a business plan,
Bud. We need cash.

10:02.640 --> 10:04.920
Oh, don't sweat it.
Trot will understand.

10:04.920 --> 10:07.280
(KELLY SCREAMS, LAUGHS)
Good news?

10:07.280 --> 10:09.400
I got an audition
with Joseph De Luca.

10:09.400 --> 10:10.560
Ohh!

10:10.560 --> 10:12.160
Can you believe it?
Are you kidding?!

10:12.160 --> 10:14.000
What took Hollywood so long?!

10:14.000 --> 10:16.360
You're the full package, babe!
Oh, babe!

10:16.360 --> 10:17.760
Oh, babe.

10:20.120 --> 10:21.880
(PHONE RINGS)
Look at you.

10:21.880 --> 10:23.720
Mm, that'll be my agent.

10:25.040 --> 10:26.520
Hello?

10:26.520 --> 10:29.040
Uh.. Yeah, he's here.

10:29.040 --> 10:31.840
Hunter, it's for you. Australia.

10:32.840 --> 10:34.920
You're a star.
Trotter?

10:34.920 --> 10:37.080
Hey, hey,
what time is it over there?

10:37.080 --> 10:38.960
It's sending-me-money time, Newbie.

10:38.960 --> 10:42.200
Well, we're on it. We're on it, mate.
Yeah, trust me.

10:42.200 --> 10:44.480
Don't 'mate' me, mate.
We have an agreement.

10:44.480 --> 10:47.520
You owe me a US licence fee.
$10,000 US.

10:48.520 --> 10:50.920
We said '30 days'
30 days ago.

10:50.920 --> 10:52.680
It's been six months since Mexico.

10:52.680 --> 10:54.560
Listen, Trot,
we're actually in the middle

10:54.560 --> 10:57.480
of an important meeting about this
right now.

10:57.480 --> 10:59.440
It's Buddy's number-one priority.

10:59.440 --> 11:03.040
End of the week, Newport.
No excuses.

11:10.480 --> 11:12.400
You coming for a surf, Dim?

11:12.400 --> 11:13.960
Nah.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.120
Ah, OK.

11:18.120 --> 11:21.320
(MOANS, GIGGLES)

11:21.320 --> 11:22.920
Oh!

11:22.920 --> 11:24.680
OK.

11:24.680 --> 11:26.760
(MOANS)

11:33.680 --> 11:35.080
Cee Cee!

11:35.080 --> 11:37.240
Hey, yeah, it's Bernie. How are you?

11:38.240 --> 11:41.160
Great, great. Hey, Um...I'm curious -

11:41.160 --> 11:44.520
are you still close with your uncle?

11:44.520 --> 11:46.320
SNAPPER: You bought all the fabric
in Thailand?

11:46.320 --> 11:47.680
I wish.

11:47.680 --> 11:50.160
These are for my bags.

11:51.200 --> 11:53.480
Yeah, Dani says
they're selling like hotcakes.

11:53.480 --> 11:55.560
Yeah. I'm really pleased.

11:55.560 --> 11:57.560
It's lucky Sharpie's away, though.

11:57.560 --> 11:59.440
Our room is wall-to-wall handbags
right now.

11:59.440 --> 12:01.520
Ah, every man's dream.
(CHUCKLES)

12:01.520 --> 12:03.120
This came too.

12:05.560 --> 12:07.560
Looks like you...

12:07.560 --> 12:10.320
..might have found your thing, huh?

12:10.320 --> 12:12.080
Yeah, I hope so.

12:12.080 --> 12:13.360
Here, mate.

12:16.640 --> 12:17.960
Problem?

12:19.480 --> 12:21.920
My stepfather died.

12:23.320 --> 12:25.200
Well, do you have to go back
for the funeral?

12:25.200 --> 12:28.560
No, it's too late.
This was sent a month ago.

12:29.560 --> 12:31.560
Margaux, I'm so sorry.

12:31.560 --> 12:34.400
We weren't close.

12:48.760 --> 12:50.480
If it isn't Nobby No-Mates.

12:50.480 --> 12:52.400
The others are coming.
Sure they are.

12:52.400 --> 12:54.480
Any chance I can get a beer
while I wait?

12:54.480 --> 12:55.960
IF they're coming.

13:00.320 --> 13:02.000
Reg.

13:03.200 --> 13:04.640
Hi, Dad.

13:04.640 --> 13:06.040
How're things?

13:06.040 --> 13:07.560
Yeah, good.

13:07.560 --> 13:09.880
You know,
got a few more board commissions,

13:09.880 --> 13:11.560
so it's pretty busy
down at the shaping shed.

13:11.560 --> 13:14.000
Yeah? They paying you well there,
are they?

13:14.000 --> 13:15.120
Enough.

13:15.120 --> 13:17.960
Yeah. Probably not as much as you'd
get plumbing, though, I'll bet.

13:17.960 --> 13:20.280
Less shit to deal with, though.

13:24.840 --> 13:29.400
(CLEARS THROAT) Um...
Look, Reg, your mum misses you.

13:29.400 --> 13:31.240
She wishes you'd, uh...

13:31.240 --> 13:33.200
..you'd visit more often.

13:33.200 --> 13:36.640
Well, maybe you and Mum
could visit me for a change.

13:36.640 --> 13:39.200
You know, come down to Bare Feet.

13:39.200 --> 13:40.640
Oh.

13:40.640 --> 13:43.080
I can give you guys a tour.

13:43.080 --> 13:44.080
Thanks.

13:44.080 --> 13:45.600
Mr Thompson, another?

13:45.600 --> 13:49.920
Uh... No, thanks, Jules.
I... I should be heading off. Um...

13:51.920 --> 13:54.080
OK, see...see ya, Reg.

13:58.160 --> 13:59.560
(SCOFFS SOFTLY)

14:05.000 --> 14:08.320
My dad hasn't spoken to me since
I moved here. (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

14:17.160 --> 14:20.160
(MAN CLICKS TONGUE)

14:24.000 --> 14:26.880
(CLICKS TONGUE)

14:39.000 --> 14:41.760
This is a very thorough application,
Danielle.

14:42.760 --> 14:45.160
What a shame
it's not for a viable business.

14:45.160 --> 14:47.560
Hairdressing salon,
that sort of thing.

14:47.560 --> 14:49.520
Surfing is growing all the time

14:49.520 --> 14:51.440
and people have more disposable
income than ever...

14:51.440 --> 14:53.200
Sorry, love,
I can't approve this loan.

14:53.200 --> 14:55.080
Even if I wanted to.

14:55.080 --> 14:56.920
So, that's it?

14:56.920 --> 15:02.160
Unless you come back in
with your father or your husband.

15:06.840 --> 15:09.520
Thanks, Merv.
Thanks for coming in.

15:09.520 --> 15:12.160
It's nice to see you
looking so smart too.

15:14.480 --> 15:17.320
(MUSIC, CHATTER)

15:18.320 --> 15:21.400
Cheer up, Dan.
Tomorrow's another day.

15:21.400 --> 15:23.600
My dad teach you to say that?

15:23.600 --> 15:25.640
You were the one who quit.

15:30.720 --> 15:32.920
TROTTER: And you are gonna love it.
And we have spare rooms...

15:32.920 --> 15:34.680
Hey, what can I get you?

15:34.680 --> 15:36.520
What? It's a good thing.
TRACY: You don't cook dinner.

15:36.520 --> 15:38.160
I always cook the dinner, Trace.

15:38.160 --> 15:39.960
Dani, Trot's gone and bought Dumbo.

15:39.960 --> 15:41.920
Don't call it that.
Well, why's it called Dumbo?

15:41.920 --> 15:44.280
It's not.
It's a white elephant.

15:44.280 --> 15:46.200
Actually, Dumbo was grey.

15:46.200 --> 15:48.560
This rich wanker
built it on top of a cliff,

15:48.560 --> 15:50.800
then his wife divorced him
before he finished it...

15:50.800 --> 15:52.320
Didn't he pork her sister?

15:52.320 --> 15:53.840
It's all very romantic.

15:53.840 --> 15:56.640
Right? And...I got it for a steal.

15:56.640 --> 15:57.840
I'm so sorry, Trace.

15:57.840 --> 15:59.000
You guys are gonna love it

15:59.000 --> 16:00.520
when you're getting pissed
on the front lawn.

16:00.520 --> 16:03.440
REGGIE: Isn't it haunted?
No, it's not haunted!

16:03.440 --> 16:04.720
No, no, no...
Reg...

16:04.720 --> 16:06.800
..it's haunted.
You can't move in there!

16:06.800 --> 16:08.320
It's not.

16:08.320 --> 16:10.360
Just deal the cards.
Do what you know. Do it well.

16:10.360 --> 16:11.600
Surprise.

16:12.840 --> 16:14.400
Hi.
(CHUCKLES)

16:19.800 --> 16:21.920
Hey. Um... I'm Tash.

16:21.920 --> 16:23.320
Hey.

16:26.840 --> 16:29.400
Um... Uh...

16:29.400 --> 16:32.520
Dani agreed
to be interviewed for my thesis -

16:32.520 --> 16:35.280
being a woman
in a male-dominated world.

16:36.280 --> 16:37.800
Surfing, obviously.

16:37.800 --> 16:38.800
Ah.
Oh.

16:38.800 --> 16:41.920
I was on my way to
a Womyn's Camp nearby, so...

16:41.920 --> 16:44.160
..I thought I'd stop in.

16:44.160 --> 16:46.520
What's your PhD?

16:46.520 --> 16:49.640
Feminist separatism
and institutional misogyny.

16:52.080 --> 16:56.320
Well, can I buy you a drink, Tash,
or am I being a...sexist pig?

16:56.320 --> 16:58.320
Vodka. Straight.

16:58.320 --> 17:00.000
Yeah?
No, I'll get it.

17:02.320 --> 17:05.360
TRACY: So, a woman's camp?

17:05.360 --> 17:11.320
Uh... Yeah, it's spelt with a Y,
though, so it's W-O-M-Y-N.

17:11.320 --> 17:13.400
Without the 'men'.

17:16.520 --> 17:19.520
(WAVES CRASH)

17:23.200 --> 17:25.240
BARRY: Is that you, love?
Uh... Yeah.

17:25.240 --> 17:27.640
Um... Dad, I've got a mate
staying over, just so you know.

17:27.640 --> 17:29.120
Uh... You need any more blankets?

17:29.120 --> 17:30.760
No, no, we're good. Thanks, Dad.

17:30.760 --> 17:32.440
Yeah, righto.
Don't let the bed bugs bite.

17:32.440 --> 17:33.560
Love you!

17:34.560 --> 17:36.760
You look really happy in this.

17:36.760 --> 17:39.280
Thanks. A friend took it.

17:39.280 --> 17:41.080
It's beautiful.

17:47.840 --> 17:49.320
Whoa.

17:49.320 --> 17:51.000
How's your dad's hearing?

17:51.000 --> 17:52.920
He's a snorer.

17:52.920 --> 17:54.800
Lucky for us.

17:56.720 --> 17:58.200
You OK?

17:58.200 --> 18:00.640
You've hardly said a word
all night.

18:00.640 --> 18:04.080
Yeah, you really
caught me off guard.

18:05.320 --> 18:07.440
Are you ashamed of me?

18:08.440 --> 18:10.040
Well...

18:10.040 --> 18:11.120
..yeah.

18:13.360 --> 18:15.280
What were you thinking?
I hardly know you.

18:15.280 --> 18:17.480
You can't just follow me here
and turn my life upside down.

18:17.480 --> 18:20.360
Firstly, I didn't follow you, OK?
I took a small detour.

18:20.360 --> 18:22.760
And second...
Shh. Just...

18:22.760 --> 18:24.600
No offence,
it's not like your friends

18:24.600 --> 18:25.840
are going to put us two together.

18:25.840 --> 18:28.480
It would literally blow their minds.

18:30.160 --> 18:32.080
How'd you know I'd be at the club?

18:32.080 --> 18:34.680
It's not like
there's anywhere else in this town.

18:39.760 --> 18:41.640
Why'd you have to wear overalls?

18:41.640 --> 18:43.920
'Cause I like overalls.

18:48.200 --> 18:51.720
Look, I'm...I'm sorry
that I just showed up.

18:52.720 --> 18:54.800
I didn't mean to scare you.

18:56.120 --> 18:58.760
I just wanted to see you again.

19:18.880 --> 19:21.760
(WAVES CRASH)

19:28.400 --> 19:31.440
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

19:36.640 --> 19:38.360
Good morning.

19:40.400 --> 19:42.400
I've gotta go.

19:48.000 --> 19:49.080
Alright.

19:49.080 --> 19:52.080
('CAN'T YOU SEE'
BY THE MARSHALL TUCKER BAND PLAYS)

19:55.640 --> 19:57.440
(WATER LAPS)

19:57.440 --> 20:00.280
# I'm gonna take a freight train

20:00.280 --> 20:02.960
# Down at the station

20:02.960 --> 20:06.920
# I don't care where it goes

20:09.440 --> 20:11.480
# Gonna climb a mountain

20:11.480 --> 20:13.440
# The highest mountain... #

20:13.440 --> 20:15.000
(WAVE RUMBLES)

20:15.000 --> 20:18.640
# And jump off
Nobody gonna know

20:19.640 --> 20:21.280
